text: it leaves me with a few concerns. first off, with the past 2 bots that sert has made, there has been a frame cutout and its been hell. granted, the kit frame is awful, but its still been hell. second, it takes away the ability to intake from the full length of the front of the bot. this means that we have to be a lot more accurate when driving swerve (and none of us have driven swerve before). Plus, due to the fact that we aren't intaking from all of the front, we run the  risk of driving over the balls and with the swerve we have, that means we wont be driving for the rest of the match. further, since we are using that space as intake space and not storage we loose the abillity to store one more ball.

text: Those are all good concerns, however I think the benefits are worth it. Being able to pick balls up directly from the floor instead of having to lift them over the frame, along with having a non- or minimally- actuated intake, would make it much easier to build. Building the frame out of 1x2 would make adding a frame cutout much easier, as we'd basically have to build a frame with two of the sides extended a little. The intake could be actuated a little such that it extends a couple inches outside the bumpers, allowing us to use mecanums, or we could have a separate centering mechanism that extends a bit. I don't think storage would be an issue; there is already enough room for at least 7-8 balls inside the bot, possibly more if I adjust the path, and I think storing a ball outside the frame perimeter is a recipe for a broken intake.
